                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> i wonder what you are thinking fluffbunny when the things you are saying are completely insane.  as some earlier poster mentioned, don't you think it is possible that mages have been complaining about lack of soloing since pop came out, we just haven't had one of their threads brought to our boards.  <br /><br />i will come clean about my love for mages.. my rl bf is a mage, has been since summer of 99.  i started my necro, first character ever so save your flames, in jan 2003.  i got lucky and hit the kei world, right when it started to be offered everywhere you looked, and before the lvl 46 nerf.. i leveled hard and fast so that i could play w/ all my rl friends that were already lvl 60.<br /><br />as me and my friends started to get flagged for the various pop zones, i found hoh.. the very first time i started kiting in the zone, way back before the group exp thing, my mage bf was all up in arms that i could effeciently get 6% a kill, latere 13% a kill, while he had to bust his ass for 1% a kill in PoD. <br /><br />seriously, get off your horse and look at things fairly for one second.  why should your luck as a necro give you the entitlement to solo and all other classes can screw themselves?  what if they nerfed solo exp in all pop zones to try to get peeps into GoD and you find all the mobs in GoD summon and stun and quad for 500?  how happy are you now that your class can no longer solo?<br /><br />finally, about the DC level pet not helping for soloing, it would.. worst case scenario it would let mages eat through trash in PoD, close to doubling their rate of exp gain.. the real help, however, would be in increasing the mages raid dps, which right now is pretty lackluster.  argue if you want, but you will not find very many mages outdamaging a wiz, rogue, or necro even including their pets output.. w/ their pet's damage, they would just like to be competitive.<br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
