                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Soloing was never intended to be a viable tactic in EQ right from the start.  In fact, they definately did not intend people to kite at all.  They recognized though that they couldn't call it an exploit to kite, so they tried to nerf kiting in a variety of ways.  For the earliest nerf attempts, read up here: <a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/archives.asp?Day=All&Month=8&Year=1999&Action=View" target="_blank">http://eq.crgaming.com/archives.asp?Day=All&Month=8&Year=1999&Action=View</a> where they talk about dots doing zero damage if the mob is in movement and not fleeing.<br /><br />That said, I do think mages need some sort of upgrade to make soloing feasible for them.  IMO, all classes should have soloing as a viable alternative to grouping, while grouping should yield better exp overall (to offset the bad groups you get).</span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
