                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Yaguex: PoP is not what I'm talking about.  PoP, as far as I can tell, was the beginning of the massive community backlash against soloing primarily because it took soloing, inadvertently or not, away from several classes that used to be able to do it very well (mages, monks, etc.)  These classes basically united and said: "SoE, give us back our soloing or make it so that no one can solo!"  <br /><br />With LDoN and now GoD, it seems to me quite clear that SoE is opting for the latter path.  Of course, they're not doing it simply to screw over soloers or to appease the whiners.  Rather, it's more of a negligence effect: SoE is "inadverdently" diminishing soloing with each new expansion through not caring about how their design decisions affect soloers.  LDoN is a prime example of this. <br /><br />It'd be hard to say that SoE is actively trying to destroy soloing and indeed they have little reason to do so and thus alienate the small group of players that do solo.  But it'd be even harder, I think, to argue that SoE still care about throwing soloers a bone. <br /><br />In other words, the greatest threat against soloing atm is negligence, and in a game like EQ, negligence can be just as powerful as nerfs in destroying a certain play style.  Just look at fear: they never nerfed it, but by choosing not to upgrade it, they just as effectively made it obsolete.<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
